        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 9:32PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 931 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorm in southern and western Coffey County, moving northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burlington, Waverly, New Strawn, Gridley, Westphalia, John Redmond
Reservoir, and Le Roy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
